tech_comments:
[2025-Apr-27 21:13:29 Anthony Styskal] OPPD  Nebraska City System Notes

UNIT #1

1. Unit 1 1FD-CP-1/2 Ground Level Transformers HST-1 & 1GAT-1
- 2 PreAction Systems 2 Tampers, 2 W/Fs, 2 Solenoids, 2 Pulls, 2 Thermistor Zones (1 per transformer), 1 H/S.
- Pulls will trip the solenoids. 

2. 1FD-CP-3/6 Ground Level Transformers 1GT and Hydrogrn Seal Oil Skid
- 2 PreAction Systems 2 Tampers, 2 W/Fs, 2 Solenoids, 2 Pulls, 2 Thermistor Zones (1 per transformer), 1 H/S.  
- Pulls will trip the solenoids.

3. 1FD-CP-4/5 Ground Level Transformers HST-2 & 1GAT-2
- 2 PreAction Systems 2 Tampers, 2 W/Fs, 2 Solenoids, 2 Pulls, 2 Thermistor Zones (1 per transformer), 1 H/S.
- Pulls will trip the solenoids.

4. Unit 1 2nd Fl Burner Rows
- 1 PreAction System 1 W/Fs, 1 Low Pressure, 1 High Pressure, 1 Solenoids, 28 Spot type heats (7 Rows of 4 Heats Covering East and West sides of burner rows), 1 H/S, 1 Bell.
- Need 1 heat and low air to trip the valve.

5. Unit 1 9th fl Tripper Bay A+B, DogHouse, and Take Up Conveyer 5A+5B
- 5 PreAction Systems: 5 W/Fs, 5 Tampers, 5 Solenoids, 1 Horn, 1 Bell.
- Tripper Deck- 3 Thermistor Zones (1 per belt 1 on ceiling) and 7 Pulls (do not trip solenoid) 
- DogHouse- 1 Thermistor Zone, 2 Pulls (do not trip solenoid)
- 5A+5B Belts- (cover upper half of belt and quarter per valve) 4 Thermistor Zones (2 per belt quartered) 4 Pulls (dont trip solenoids)
- 5A+5B belts are quarter sections. The 2 upper quarters go to the 9th fl panel and the bottom 2 quarters go down to the crusher house. There is a pull station on each side of the dividing walls/doors that trip the audibles but do not trip solenoids.
Tripper Bay thermistor zones on the belts, any one zone will trip Both valves and flow both belts.

6. Unit 1 11th fl Dust Collectors A+B (Roof)
- 2 PreAction Systems: 2 W/Fs, 2 Tampers, 2 Solenoids, 1 Horn, 1 Bell
- 4 Spot Type Heats (2 per dust collector 1 inside and 1 underneath) 2 Pulls (1 per collector)
- Each dust collector has 2 heats. 1 is in the bottom portion where you walk in (testable) and the other is piped off of that heat and mounts inside the collector (not accessible)

7. Unit 1 Control Room
- 39 smokes, 24 heats, 6 ducts, 5 pulls, 1 W/F (lube oil filter room), 1 tamper (Lube oil filter room), 4 h/s
- Heats: 4 ground level Generator rm, 9 Boiler feed pump heats, vestibule addressable heat, outside elevator, Unit 1 cntrl rm lunch rm?, 8 carpenters shop
- Smokes: 21 control room, 3 battery rooms ground level, 15 cable spread room
- ducts: 2 main control room ducts, 4 centrifugal vent fans?

8. Unit 1 Ground FD & ID Fluid Fan Drives
- 6 PreAction Systems 6 W/Fs, 6 Low Airs, 6 Solenoids
- 6 Spot type heats (1 per drive), 1 H/S
- Need 1 heat and low air to trip the valve.

9. Unit 1 Ground Level Boiler Feed Pumps, Lube Oil Pulverizer Pump, and Unit 1 Turbine
- 2 PreAction Systems & 1 Wet System: 3 W/Fs, 2 Tampers, 2 Low Pressure, 1 High Pressure, 2 Solenoids
- 20 Spot Type Heats (Turbine 9, Pulverizers 7, Boiler Feed Pumps 4), 1 H/S
- Each turbine heat is individually addressed. 1 heat per pulverizer (7 total) and takes Low air + Heat to trip the solenoid.  There are 13 total heats on the Boiler Feed Pumps (2 pumps) but only the heats on each side of the bearing on the 2 pumps (4 total heats) trip the Turbine valve. The other remaining heats that are mounted high up around the pumps report to the Unit 1 control room panel and are all on 1 circuit.

10. Unit 1 Mezz Level Lube Oil Reservoir 1697
- 1 PreAction System 1 W/Fs, 2 Tampers, 1 Solenoids
- 1 Pull, 1 Thermistor Zone, 1 H/S

11. Water Treatment Building

12. Warehouse Building

13. Admin,Steam Fitters,Tool Rm,Oil Stor,I&C,Mach Shop

14. Wood Shop/Carpenters Shop 
- 1 wet system 1 W/F, 1 Tamper, 1 Bell, 1 H/S
- Local Allison panel by riser. Heats report to Control 1

UNIT #2

14. Ammonia building/tank System (Fike Cheetah) 
- Covers the ammonia tank outside of Unit 2. An ammonia detecting device is what trips the solenoid. Could not test this device. Manually tripped the PreAction System.
- Need to let control room know when testing this system because it will alert their DCS system When alarmed.

15. (Node 3) Boiler Feed Pumps A&B: Ground Level 925
- 4 W/F, 5 Tamper, 2 High Pressure, 2 Low Pressure, 2 Solenoid
- 1 Addressable Heat, 12 Spot Type Heats, 3 Bells, 1Chime, 2 Duct Smokes
- 2 PreAction Systems and 2 Wet System
- 6 Heats 1 Bell per pump
- Diesel Fire Pump Room has 2 Duct Smokes and 1 W/F 1 Tamper

16. (Node 10) Burner Fronts 247, 249, 251, 253, 255: Ground Level 925
- 5 W/F, 6 Tamper, 5 High Pressure, 5 Low Pressure, 5 Solenoids
- 1 Addressable Heat, 55 Spot Type Heats, 6 Bells, 1Chime, 4 Vesdas (8th fl)
- 5 PreAction Systems
- 5th fl West Side Burner Heats (Module 45) Trips B/W Valve 251 (11 total heats 1 bell)
- 5th fl East Side Burner Heats (module 39) Trips M/E Valve 255 (11 total heats 1 bell)
- 6th fl West Side Burner Heats (Module 37) Trips B/E Valve 253 (11 total heats 1 bell)
- 6th fl East Side Burner Heats (Module 43) Trips M/W Valve 249 (11 total heats 1 bell)
- 7th fl West Side Burner Heats (Module 41) Trips T/W Valve 247 (11 total heats 1 bell)

17. (Node 9) FD/PA Fan Lube Oil 222&224: Ground Level 925
- 3 W/F, 3 Tamper, 2 High Pressure, 2 Low Pressure,
- 1 Addressable Heat, 1 Bells, 1Chime,
- 2 Dry Systems and 1 Manual Sprinkler System
- Loss of air trips dry valves
18. (Node 8) FD/PA Fan Lube Oil 239&241: Ground Level 925
- 4 W/F, 4 Tamper, 3 High Pressure, 3 Low Pressure,
- 1 Addressable Heat, 1 Bells, 1Chime,
- 3 Dry Systems and 1 Manual Sprinkler System
- Loss of air trips dry valves

19. (Node 4) Mezz Level HST-1, HST-2, Dirty/Clean Oil Tank, Turbine Lube Oil Reservoir, Turbine Bearing & Turbine Underfloor
- 7 W/F, 9 Tamper, 6 High Pressure, 6 Low Pressure, 2 Solenoids
- 1 Addressable Heat, 30 Spot Type Heats (Turbine&Turbine Underfloor), 5 Bells, 2 Chime
- 6 PreAction Systems 1 Wet System
- Turbine & underfloor valves have an annunciator for the Node 4 fire panel next to them. Turbine heats are indeividually addressed. Turbine Underfloor heats are all on module 105 (located in Red FP box #4 in Cage by Node 5 panel above electrical Cabinets). Unhook wire from the module and attached them to a meter to test faster. 9 turbine heats 21 under turbine heats. Heats do not shut down turbine.  Transformer are covered by a closed head/deluge system. No electric tripping.

20. (Node 5) Mezz Level Main Power Transformer, GST-1, GST-2, Control Room FM-200, Battery Room, Battery Charging Room
- 3 W/F, 4 Tamper, 3 High Pressure, 3 Low Pressure,1 Addressable Heat, 31 smokes (11 control rm, 5 battery, 10 electrical, 5 inverter), 5 Bells, 2 Chime, 2 VESDAs (above control room)
- 6 PreAction Systems 1 Wet System
- FM-200 System covers the Unit 2 control room: 2 Pulls 2 aborts 11 smokes, 2 bells, 1 horn, 1 strobe, 1 pressure switch, 1 solenoid bypass.
- Turbine & underfloor valves have an annunciator for the Node 4 fire panel next to them. Turbine heats are indeividually addressed. Turbine Underfloor heats are all on module 105 (located in Red FP box #4 in Cage by Node 5 panel above electrical Cabinets). Unhook wire from the module and attached them to a meter to test faster. 9 turbine heats 21 underturbine heats. Heats do not shut down turbine.
- Transformers are closed head system with deluge. No electric tripping.
- Unit 2 Control Room is covered by FM-200 tanks are outside of the control room by the windows looking at Unit 2 turbine deck. No EPO

21. (Node 7) Pulverizer Lube Oil Tanks: Ground Level 925
- 1 W/F, 2 Tamper, 1 High Pressure, 1 Low Pressure, 1 Solenoid, 1 Addressable Heat, 10 Spot Type Heats, 11 Bells, 1Chime
- 2 heats per pulverizer
- 2 Bells per pulverizer

22. (Node 11) SDA Motor & Atomizer 11th floor
- 2 W/F, 3 Tamper, 2 High Pressure, 2 Low Pressure, 1 Addressable Heat, 1 Bell, 1 Chime, 1 Pull
- 2 PreAction Systems-must bring water bucket to reset PreAction valve.

23. (Node 6) Tripper Belts 191, 193, 195, 197, 199 Panel 2FPA-095-PL
- 5 W/F, 6 Tamper, 1 High Pressure, 1 Low Pressure, 4 Solenoid
- 1 Addressable Heat, 5 Thermistor Zones, 5 pulls,1 Bell, 1Chime
- 4 PreAction Systems and 1 Dry System
- 2 Thermistor zones per belt. The 5th zone must cover the ceiling. (Notifier node 6 program shows 5 thermistor zones).  Pull stations will trip solenoids.
- Any alarm will shut the belts down. Must do inspection while they are not running coal.

COAL HANDLING

24. Bucket Wheel Reclaimer & Electrical Room on Reclaimer
- 19 Heats, 1 Pull, 2 h/s, 2 Bells
- Heats on the reclaimer trip the solenoid in the transfer house to trip the Deluge valve. System will only trip if the fire hose from the discharge piping is hooked up the the reclaimer hose valve.
- Ecaro has 6 heats 1 bell 1 h/s 1 abort 1 pull 1 EPO 1 actuator.
- There is an Ecaro suppression tank that covers the electrical room on the reclaimer.This has 6 heats that cross zone to trip the actuator. Will need to disable relay 1 that shuts power down to the reclaimer.
25. Crusher House / Control Room / Heavy Equip Bldg

tech_comments:
[2025-Feb-27 16:40:07 Gerald Bartlett] (John Twitty Energy Center)
                Take Down Procedure
Steps:
Contact Control Room let them know service work is being done.
Close Nitrogen Cylinders Valves Front and Rear
 of Turbine A, Turbine B, Generator.
(Marked 1-6)
Remove Solenoids from Front Nitrogen     Cylinder of Turbine A, Turbine B, Generator. 
Note- Added level of safety if desired is to remove the Front Nitrogen Cylinders discharge hose directly over the solenoids on Turbine A, Turbine B, Generator. 
(Marked with Red Paint)

            (John Twitty Energy Center)
                Cylinder drain and refill
Note: Do Front bank and then do Rear bank separately. 

(Drain down)
Remove pilot tank hoses but leave connector on cylinder.
Attach air compressor hose and adapter connector hose.
Remove plugs from outside discharge lines and attach discharge hose to direct the flow of water away. 
Attach air from air compressor and blow tanks down until no water flows anymore and cycle tank air up and down with the block valve on the discharge piping to allow the air compressor to build up pressure and this will take numerous cycles. Be patient it takes a little while. Dont remove the air supply hose until most of the water is out as the back pressure will then push water back through the hose connecting point. 
Remove air compressor and now install smaller adapter to cylinder in the rear so the air connector fits, it has a smaller connection point on the tank. 
Now repeat the blow down on the rear cylinders.

(Refill Front and Rear Cylinders)
GO SLOWLY IT REFILLS BETTER!!!
Close System block valve.
Remove pressure gauge from cylinder next to pressure switch. 
Attach water fill hose adapter. Make sure you have the shutoff adapter attached to the end of the hose in the hut so you can control the water from inside the hut.
Loosen all 3 indicator plugs.
Wrap a rag or rags around the neck to catch the water as you fill each cylinder. It keeps the mess down.
Plug the inlet on the pilot cylinder.
Now turn water on slowly and allow air to flow through the indicators doing one at a time until the all 3 cylinders are full.
Turn water off.
Tighten all 3 indicator plugs and Green indicator should be up. 
Remove water attachment and reinstall gauge.
Remove plug from pilot tank. 
Dry everything up and reattach regular hose connections.

Note: Do the exact same thing for the Rear but you must use the smaller adapter for plugging the initial tank. The one that you have used for the air attachment is the right one to use.
Dry all connections well to prevent standing water in the hoses and fittings.
DONT FORGET TO INSTALL THE FIELD PIPE PLUGS!! 
*Return all solenoids and open Nitrogen valves to return system to normal service.
 The whole process will take 7-8 hours.
